story.title: My Confidant - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: When Lucy hears a stranger break into her apartment, she texts her long-distance boyfriend, Brendan. Too bad there’s nothing he can do to save her…
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: Do you hear that clunking noise?
It sounds like someone stomping around.
OMG, I’m too afraid to look out my bedroom door…
Is there someone in our apartment?
Answer me! You always respond to my texts…
Okay, now I’m COMPLETELY creeped out.
He lives halfway across the country in New York,
But Lucy hopes he can make her feel better.
I know--I think I’d recognize my gf’s number.
This isn’t funny--I think there’s someone in my apartment.
Are you sure it’s not your upstairs neighbors?
Yeah. It sounds closer than that
It’s a clunking noise, like someone in heavy boots is walking around in my living room
And Topher isn’t answering my texts.
I don’t know why you live with that tool in Detroit when you could live in NYC with me.
Let’s not get into that now--there’s someone in my FREAKING apartment!
OMG, now someone’s knocking on my bedroom door!
I called out his name but he didn’t answer.
Maybe he didn’t hear you respond and didn’t want to wake you
You’re not being very supportive right now.
You could lock your bedroom door to be extra safe.
I’m so scared I don’t even want to get out of bed
What if the intruder has a gun and shoots me through the door?
I locked the door…do you think it’s secure?
Luce, no one is going to pick your lock. You’re imagining things.
OMG! I think they heard me--now they’re BANGING on the door
He’s saying that if I don’t open it, I’ll never see my friend again.
There IS someone in your apartment.
This is bad--you have to get out of there
Can you climb down your fire escape?
Luce, there’s an intruder in your apartment.
Topher might not even be alive.
For once in your life put yourself first
Luce, I can’t really think straight right now…
My girlfriend could be attacked any minute.
I hate that you live there.
Shit, wasn’t that Congressman just shot out there?
Goddammit! I wish you were still in New York.
I’d be at your apartment right now if you were.
I wish you’d never taken that art residency out there
It’s always been felt so impossible–you being so far away
But Brendan, I had to follow my dreams
Feels more like a nightmare tonight.
I know. Stay on the phone with me?
Yeah, and my bedroom light is off.
What? Can’t blame a guy for trying
I haven’t seen you in 3 weeks.
You know you’re always welcome to visit
You know I can’t always visit, Luce
You just paint over there with Topher
This whole art residency thing was his idea in the first place.
You don’t think that I hate it here too right now?
I’m scared to death and I’m trapped in my apartment!
Brendan, when I’m in Detroit, painting…
I’m never going to let you take that away from me.
I know you didn’t mean that.
Do you think he can break down the door?
God, don’t scare me like that.
I don’t like it either, Luce
What if he knows how to pick the locks?
Luce, you’ve got to listen to me
I know you don’t want to leave Topher, but you’re got to get out of that building
That guy figured out a way to get into your apartment…
Do you have those iron safety bars on your window?
Go out your window and down the fire escape.
I can’t! It’s outside Topher’s window, not mine.
Is Topher’s window close to yours?
But I might have to jump.
Okay. You’re on the second floor, right?
With only one story below you?
I think you should do it.
Yeah. It actually helps a lot.
And don’t text me again until you’re a few blocks away.
Omg, Luce, we forgot to say I love you
So you still love me, huh?
No, I’m sitting in the back of the police car for protection. The police are in my apartment.
It’s okay--I must’ve left my apartment at the perfect time
Right after I turned the corner, the cops came down the street.
I flagged them down and I looked crazy, I mean, absolutely crazy
I’m still in my pj’s and I’m barefoot.
You’re alive so you’d look perfect to me no matter what you were wearing.
Haha, you have to say stuff like that because you’re my boyfriend.
It’s strange sitting back here with sirens going.
I don’t like the idea of you being in a cop car like that.
I know. There’s a cop in the front but he’s quiet.
And it’s weird, because another cop went into my apartment building
A couple other cops went up after her…
Like, after she’d been up there awhile.
I’m okay. My heartbeat’s slowing down.
I’m pretty damn terrified, so please--
I’m still in the police car, but the cops came down from my apartment
